<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D6BFF8CFF4DF856FCFDF84B" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="207B96733D6BFF8CFF4DF856FCFDF84B" blockId="24.[151,1437,1698,2013]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D6BFF8CFF4DF856FEA5F82F" bold="true" box="[199,334,1951,1977]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a patronym in honor of Martín Ramírez, who has greatly contributed to taxonomic and systematic studies of Neotropical spiders.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="74BBC6FB3D6AFF8DFF1DF922FD6FF8F9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468407" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4468407" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468407/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" startId="25.[151,250,1771,1795]" targetBox="[151,1436,201,1748]" targetPageId="25">
<paragraph id="207B96733D6AFF8DFF1DF922FD6FF8F9" blockId="25.[151,1437,1771,1904]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D6AFF8DFF1DF922FEBBF892" bold="true" box="[151,336,1771,1796]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">FIGURE 12A–D.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D6AFF8DFEDDF925FDEBF895" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[343,512,1772,1795]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramirezi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D6AFF8DFEDDF925FDEBF895" box="[343,512,1772,1795]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Patrera ramirezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D6AFF8DFD8CF925FDD4F892" bold="true" box="[518,575,1772,1796]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0983F71A3D6AFF8DFD8CF925FDD4F892" box="[518,575,1772,1796]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Male: (AMNH): A habitus, dorsal view; C right palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: dps, dorsal projection of the subtegulum; FD, fertilization ducts; SR, seminal receptacles. Scale bars: A–B: 2.16mm; C:1mm; D–E: 0.66mm; F–G: 0.25mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D6AFF8EFF4DF854FD47FF43" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="207B96733D6AFF8EFF4DF854FD47FF43" blockId="25.[151,1437,1949,2012]" lastBlockId="26.[151,1437,151,1149]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D6AFF8DFF4DF854FEA9F821" bold="true" box="[199,322,1949,1975]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D6AFF8DFE3AF856FD81F82E" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[432,618,1951,1976]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramirezi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D6AFF8DFE3AF856FD81F82E" box="[432,618,1951,1976]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Patrera ramirezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D6AFF8DFDFAF857FD45F82E" bold="true" box="[624,686,1950,1976]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0983F71A3D6AFF8DFDFAF857FD45F82E" box="[624,686,1950,1976]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be differentiated from those of the remaining species of the genus by their long retrolateral tibial apophysis, with small dorsal projection (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D6AFF8DFC6BF80BFBDBF84A" box="[993,1072,1986,2012]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-18@25.[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 12A–D. Patrera ramirezi n. sp. Male: (AMNH): A habitus, dorsal view; C right palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations: dps, dorsal projection of the subtegulum; FD, fertilization ducts; SR, seminal receptacles. Scale bars:A–B: 2.16mm; C:1mm; D–E: 0.66mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468407" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468407/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
C–E). Females are distinguished by their epigynum with exceptionally wide, transversal hood, and transversal copulatory ducts with small seminal receptacles, anteriorly positioned (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D69FF8EFD93FF72FD82FF43" box="[537,617,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-18@25.[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 12A–D. Patrera ramirezi n. sp. Male: (AMNH): A habitus, dorsal view; C right palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations: dps, dorsal projection of the subtegulum; FD, fertilization ducts; SR, seminal receptacles. Scale bars:A–B: 2.16mm; C:1mm; D–E: 0.66mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468407" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468407/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
F–G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D69FF8EFF4DFF17FAD3FBCF" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph id="207B96733D69FF8EFF4DFF17FBA7FD13" blockId="26.[151,1437,151,1149]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D69FF8EFF4DFF17FEB2FF6E" bold="true" box="[199,345,222,248]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D69FF8EFEEAFF16FE71FF6F" box="[352,410,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="FF7F28D13D69FF8EFE23FF16FDFDFF6F" box="[425,534,223,249]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Holotype</typeStatus>
, AMNH). Cephalothorax and legs brown-reddish (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D69FF8EFBDBFF16FB51FF6F" box="[1105,1210,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-18@25.[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 12A–D. Patrera ramirezi n. sp. Male: (AMNH): A habitus, dorsal view; C right palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations: dps, dorsal projection of the subtegulum; FD, fertilization ducts; SR, seminal receptacles. Scale bars:A–B: 2.16mm; C:1mm; D–E: 0.66mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468407" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468407/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
). Abdomen dorsally gray with dark spots from median to posterior area; ventrally white (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D69FF8EFC23FECAFBF8FE8B" box="[937,1043,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-18@25.[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 12A–D. Patrera ramirezi n. sp. Male: (AMNH): A habitus, dorsal view; C right palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations: dps, dorsal projection of the subtegulum; FD, fertilization ducts; SR, seminal receptacles. Scale bars:A–B: 2.16mm; C:1mm; D–E: 0.66mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468407" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468407/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
). Total length 5.1, carapace length 2.6, width 2.02. Clypeus height 0.08. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.06, ALE 0.10, PME 0.10, PLE 0.06; AME–AME 0.06, AME–ALE 0.06, PME–PME 0.12, PME–PLE 0.08, ALE–PLE 0.02. Chelicerae 0.72 long, four promarginal teeth, six retromarginal denticles. Leg measurements: leg I—femur 2.9/ patella 1.0/ tibia 3.0/ metatarsus 2.7/ tarsus 1.3/ total 10.9; II—2.6/ 1.0/ 1.62/ 2.8/ 1.05/ 9.07; III—1.8/ 0.8/ 1.4/ 1.6/ 0.7/ 6.3; IV—2.63/ 0.8/ 2.15/ 2.8/ 0.9/ 9.28. Leg spination: I—tibia v2-2-0, metatarsus v2-2-0, p1-1-0, r1-1-0; II—tibia v2-2-0, metatarsus v2-2-0, p1-1-0, r1-1-0; III—tibia v2-2-1, p0-1-1, r0-1-1; IV—tibia v2-2-1, p0-1-1, r0-1-1; Abdomen: length 2.5, epigastric furrow 0.9 from tracheal spiracle, spiracle 1.0 from base of spinnerets. Palp: retrolateral tibial apophysis long, ventrally projected; cymbium longer than tibia; subtegulum longer than wide with flattened and apically subrounded distal projection; tegulum longer than wide; median apophysis laminar, short and medially situated; embolus long, apically filiform with narrow base and basally inserted on the tegulum (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D69FF8EFC33FDA2FBE2FD13" box="[953,1033,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-18@25.[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 12A–D. Patrera ramirezi n. sp. Male: (AMNH): A habitus, dorsal view; C right palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations: dps, dorsal projection of the subtegulum; FD, fertilization ducts; SR, seminal receptacles. Scale bars:A–B: 2.16mm; C:1mm; D–E: 0.66mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468407" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468407/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
C–E).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="207B96733D69FF8EFF4DFD46FF1DFBA3" blockId="26.[151,1437,151,1149]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D69FF8EFF4DFD46FEF0FD3F" box="[199,283,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Female</emphasis>
(AMNH, 
<typeStatus id="FF7F28D13D69FF8EFE1BFD46FE13FD3F" box="[401,504,655,681]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Paratype</typeStatus>
). Coloration as in the male (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D69FF8EFCBDFD46FC74FD3F" box="[823,927,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-18@25.[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 12A–D. Patrera ramirezi n. sp. Male: (AMNH): A habitus, dorsal view; C right palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations: dps, dorsal projection of the subtegulum; FD, fertilization ducts; SR, seminal receptacles. Scale bars:A–B: 2.16mm; C:1mm; D–E: 0.66mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468407" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468407/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
). Total length 5.8, carapace length 2.9, width 2.1. Clypeus height 0.10. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.06, ALE 0.12, PME 0.14, PLE 0.12; AME– AME 0.04, AME–ALE 0.06, PME–PME 0.16, PME–PLE 0.10, ALE–PLE 0.04. Chelicerae 1.0 long, four promarginal teeth, five retromarginal denticles. Leg measurements: leg I—femur 2.52/ patella 0.9/ tibia 2.5/ metatarsus 2.1/ tarsus 1.0/ total 9.02; II—2.45/ 0.9/ 2.3/ 2.1/ 0.9/ 8.65; III—1.8/ 0.9/ 1.4/ 1.6/ 0.7/ 6.4; IV—2.5/ 0.9/ 2.0/ 2.6/ 0.9/ 8.9. Leg spination: I—tibia v2-2-0, metatarsus p1-1-0, r1-1-0; II—tibia v2-2-0, metatarsus v2-2-0, p1-1-0, r1-1-0; III—tibia p0-1-1, r0-1-1; IV—tibia v2-2-1, p0-1-1, r0-1-1; Abdomen: length 2.85, epigastric furrow 0.8 from tracheal spiracle, spiracle 1.0 from base of spinnerets. Epigynum: hood transversal, very wide and posteriorly projected; lateral borders weakly sclerotized, parallel, wide and apically rounded; atrium long and ample; internally with copulatory ducts long and wide; seminal receptacles small, rounded and anteriorly situated on the copulatory ducts; spermathecae large, oval and anteriorly positioned; fertilization ducts almost as long as spermathecae (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D69FF8EFAE5FC3EFF59FBA3" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-18@25.[151,1436,201,1748]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 12A–D. Patrera ramirezi n. sp. Male: (AMNH): A habitus, dorsal view; C right palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations: dps, dorsal projection of the subtegulum; FD, fertilization ducts; SR, seminal receptacles. Scale bars:A–B: 2.16mm; C:1mm; D–E: 0.66mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468407" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468407/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
F–G).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="207B96733D69FF8EFF4DFBF7FAD3FBCF" blockId="26.[151,1437,151,1149]" box="[199,1336,1086,1113]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D69FF8EFF4DFBF7FED4FBCE" bold="true" box="[199,319,1086,1112]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Variation.</emphasis>
Males (n=3): total length: 6.83–7.33; carapace length: 3.07–3.44; femur I length 2.9–3.68.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
